title: Catfish Saint James
summary: Need a pescatarian main course? Catfish Saint James could be a spectacular recipe to try. One serving contains 1845 calories, 101g of protein, and 119g of fat. This recipe serves 4. For $9.02 per serving, this recipe covers 55% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. It is brought to you by Allrecipes. 6 people have made this recipe and would make it again. If you have evaporated milk, garlic powder, flour, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the flour you could follow this main course with the Apple Tart with Caramel Sauce as a dessert. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about 8 hours and 45 minutes. Overall, this recipe earns an amazing spoonacular score of 87%. Try Saint Eldercot, Coquille Saint-Jacques, and Coquilles Saint Jacques for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir are my top picks for Catfish. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. You could try Tiamo Pinot Grigio. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 11 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Tiamo Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: Light straw yellow color. Fresh and rich fruity aromas of apple and pear with a hint of citrus fruit that fade into the floral bouquet. Fresh and fruity, very clean and crisp.Tiamo Pinot Grigio pairs well with a wide array of lighter cuisine, especially fish/shellfish, poultry, pastas in cream sauce and softer cheeses. It's also an ideal aperitif.

instructions: Wash and dry catfish filets. Place filets in a shallow dish and pour milk over them. Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.                        Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, cheese, Italian seasoning, baking powder, garlic powder, dry mustard, onion powder, salt and pepper. Dredge filets in flour mixture.                        Lightly grease a rimmed baking sheet and place coated filets in pan. Drizzle melted butter over filets.                        Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes, or until firm and flaky.  Serve hot.
